you want to use essay plans.

00:01:16.560 --> 00:01:18.159
so literally, for re,

00:01:18.160 --> 00:01:19.199
what I would do is

00:01:19.200 --> 00:01:21.199
I would answer as many of the past

00:01:21.200 --> 00:01:22.759
paper questions as I could,

00:01:22.760 --> 00:01:23.959
and I would plan the.

00:01:23.960 --> 00:01:25.159
the 12 markers.

00:01:25.160 --> 00:01:26.759
I wouldn't actually write them.

00:01:26.760 --> 00:01:27.719
like all of them.

00:01:27.720 --> 00:01:29.260
but I would plan them

00:01:29.640 --> 00:01:30.900
like history.

00:01:31.040 --> 00:01:32.879
they like to recycle questions.

00:01:32.880 --> 00:01:33.799
like, I'm not kidding,

00:01:33.800 --> 00:01:37.100
one of the 12 markers was literally the reverse

00:01:37.320 --> 00:01:40.959
of one of the questions in a past people question.

00:01:40.960 --> 00:01:43.919
and one of the 5 markers was literally word for word

00:01:43.920 --> 00:01:46.559
for the 2021 paper, I believe.

00:01:46.560 --> 00:01:49.220
also, unlike English and history,

00:01:49.240 --> 00:01:51.519
if you stick to a certain structure in RE,

00:01:51.520 --> 00:01:52.900
you'll get the marks.

00:01:53.840 --> 00:01:55.799
so when it comes to your structure and your answers,

00:01:55.800 --> 00:01:57.279
it's very repetitive.

00:01:57.280 --> 00:02:00.199
like, you don't need to sound like you're doing a lot.

00:02:00.200 --> 00:02:02.079
you need to stick to saying your point,

00:02:02.080 --> 00:02:03.279
your evident explanation,

00:02:03.280 --> 00:02:04.759
and then you link it back to the question

00:02:04.760 --> 00:02:05.940
and then you're done.

00:02:06.360 --> 00:02:08.439
what I did in the paper was that

00:02:08.440 --> 00:02:10.479
I would do the 12 markers first,

00:02:10.480 --> 00:02:11.879
and then I would do the 5 marker,

00:02:11.880 --> 00:02:12.559
then the full marker,

00:02:12.560 --> 00:02:13.620
then the 3 marker,

00:02:13.680 --> 00:02:15.239
because then it put my mind at ease

00:02:15.240 --> 00:02:18.300
because I got out the bigger chunk of the paper first.

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:20.079
what I was told

00:02:20.080 --> 00:02:21.180
and when I found out

00:02:21.320 --> 00:02:23.239
is that you don't need to know the sources

00:02:23.240 --> 00:02:24.159
word for word.

00:02:24.160 --> 00:02:26.500
literally could be like in Marx gospel

00:02:27.600 --> 00:02:29.039
and then explain the source.

00:02:29.040 --> 00:02:31.839
if you don't know the source. however,

00:02:31.840 --> 00:02:33.999
I would still recommend that you remember the sources

00:02:34.000 --> 00:02:35.039
just in case

00:02:35.040 --> 00:02:37.820
the examiner you get is quite picky.

